class Solution {
    public int findLUSlength(String a, String b) {
        if (a.equals(b)) {
            return -1;
        } else {
            return Math.max(a.length(), b.length());
        }
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution takes advantage of the fact that if two strings are equal, there are no uncommon subsequences, so it returns -1. If the strings are not equal, the longest uncommon subsequence will be the longer string itself, as it cannot be a subsequence of the shorter string. This approach has a constant time complexity because string comparison and length calculation are constant time operations in Java.

